An erotic, tension filled thriller where two girls become involved in a romantic relationship. Complications arise when one of the girls accidentally kills the other girl&#039;s mother. Attempting to flee, the girls become the target of a band of malicious thugs who try to destroy them and demolish their gas station. The film explodes in a high-octane conclusion. GASOLINE is the directorial debut of Italian filmmaker Monica Stambrini, who also served as co-screenwriter, and stars Maya Sansa and Regina Orioli in the lead roles.
